==Portuguese==

===Verb===
'''ser'''

# Denotes a permantent quality; to [[be]];
#:"''Ela '''é''' bonita.''" - She is beautiful (permanent quality).
# Denotes location in time; to [[be]];
#:"''Que horas '''são'''?''" - What time is it? (lit: "''What hours are?''")
#:"'''''São''' cinco horas.''" - It is five o'clock. (lit.: "''Are five hours''")
# Auxiliary verb for the passive voice, precedes verb in participle; to [[be]].
#:"''O carro '''foi''' vendido pelo seu antigo dono.''" - The car have been sold by its old owner.

====Etymology====
Latin ''esse'' (to be)

